===Etymology===
; "hole":
: {{ety|zh|:inh|sit-pro:*(g/k)uŋ<t:hole; orifice; inner part>}}
: From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*(g/k)uŋ||hole; orifice; inner part}}. {{och-l|孔|hole}} is probably the endoactive derivation of {{och-l|空|id=1|hollow; empty}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Cognate with {{cog|bo|ཁུང||hole}}, {{cog|kac|ladi '''hku'''|tr=lədî hkū|t=nostril}}, {{cog|cdm|घाङ्‌|tr=gʰaŋ|t=hole}}, {{cog|my|အခေါင်း||hollow place; cavity}}, {{cog|nxq|kho³³||cave; hole; pit}} (STEDT).

; "peacock":
: Starostin reconstructs {{och-l|孔|tr=*khōŋ}} and compares it to {{cog|mkh-vie-pro|*k-voːŋ}}. Compare also {{cog|sea|kuwok}}, {{cog|ssm|kwɔːŋ}}.

